This paper discusses time synchronization in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and distributed computing (DC). The paper also proposes a tree structured approach, which falls under the category of system and control (SY) and data structures (DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of TDMA (Time Division Multiple Access), which is a topic related to information theory (IT). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NI and cs.DC, followed by cs.SY, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
